cop noun short for copper:  one who cops, from capere, Latin and Old French 
capere: to capture. 

As a verb, cop is used colloquially to take, especially fraudulently, 
as in "copping a plea" (referring to a felon taking the offer of prosecutors 
to reduced charges, pleading guilty to a [[misdemeanor]], saving the government 
the [[inconvenience]] and expense of a trial).